WEBVTT

1
00:00:21.031 --> 00:00:25.031
- Ibrahim
X : @sle1i

2
00:00:25.197 --> 00:00:29.197
Street-talk translation

3
00:00:29.363 --> 00:00:31.031
You with the patient?

4
00:00:32.658 --> 00:00:34.659
Outside her room. ma'am.

5
00:00:34.660 --> 00:00:37.538
Bet. Pass along a message to her nurse.

6
00:00:41.875 --> 00:00:43.275
What are you even doing here?

7
00:00:43.669 --> 00:00:45.712
Just came to keep you company.

8
00:00:48.799 --> 00:00:54.512
You can start the paperwork for me to
get an interim mayor locked in.

9
00:00:54.513 --> 00:00:59.016
Is she in that bad shape?
-She's fading fast. Catch you at home.

10
00:00:59.017 --> 00:01:04.565
The voice still wants the same thing. but
the gas in the mine wasn't enough. right?

11
00:01:05.566 --> 00:01:07.775
That gas was meant for Lukas Kyle.

12
00:01:07.776 --> 00:01:09.360
Was he even in the mine?

13
00:01:09.361 --> 00:01:10.761
Bro bounced.

14
00:01:11.655 --> 00:01:13.490
The mayor didn't. though.

15
00:01:17.244 --> 00:01:20.581
Well. sounds like the voice
is totally cool with that.

16
00:01:22.124 --> 00:01:23.625
A heroic vibe to go out on.

17
00:01:25.335 --> 00:01:26.735
And this right here...

18
00:01:27.880 --> 00:01:30.747
might make drugging the whole Silo unnecessary.

19
00:01:34.469 --> 00:01:35.869
I'll handle it for you.

20
00:01:38.682 --> 00:01:42.603
I gotta become mayor.
-Yeah. I get it.

21
00:01:43.896 --> 00:01:46.029
You don't gotta do it all by yourself.

22
00:01:51.486 --> 00:01:53.446
When's Mrs Sims showing up?

23
00:01:53.447 --> 00:01:54.847
She's on her way.

24
00:01:56.617 --> 00:01:58.619
She wants her knocked out cold.

25
00:02:03.874 --> 00:02:05.274
Grab her.

26
00:02:11.715 --> 00:02:13.115
What's going down?

27
00:02:18.764 --> 00:02:20.848
It's all good.
-Help.

28
00:02:20.849 --> 00:02:24.269
Hold her still.
-Help.

29
00:03:12.985 --> 00:03:15.696
We gotta dip. Now.

30
00:04:55.546 --> 00:04:57.813
BASED ON THE SILO SERIES BY HUGH HOWEY

31
00:05:14.106 --> 00:05:17.066
Yo. What are you doing?
-We gotta call someone.

32
00:05:17.067 --> 00:05:18.527
Call someone?

33
00:05:19.152 --> 00:05:20.236
What are you doing?

34
00:05:20.237 --> 00:05:22.446
They made him vanish.
-What the actual fuck.

35
00:05:22.447 --> 00:05:24.657
They're totally tapping our phones.

36
00:05:24.658 --> 00:05:27.244
What if Charlotte calls?
-You can't…

37
00:05:27.369 --> 00:05:30.079
They're watching Charlotte's phone too.

38
00:05:30.080 --> 00:05:33.833
We gotta bounce. I don't even know if my ride is safe…

39
00:05:33.834 --> 00:05:35.377
What do you think is going on?

40
00:05:38.255 --> 00:05:41.508
Some suits just made that dude disappear.

41
00:05:45.554 --> 00:05:47.754
So we gotta head somewhere else.

42
00:05:50.976 --> 00:05:52.602
I know a spot.

43
00:05:52.603 --> 00:05:54.003
Where?

44
00:05:56.607 --> 00:06:00.068
Alright. Don't show before 10.

45
00:06:01.195 --> 00:06:02.795
What am I supposed to do till then?

46
00:06:03.572 --> 00:06:05.449
Don't head home.

47
00:06:10.204 --> 00:06:11.622
It's gonna be fine. Help.

48
00:06:17.377 --> 00:06:20.838
Is she okay?
-No clue. They wouldn't let me stay.

49
00:06:20.839 --> 00:06:22.924
I'm such a dumbass.
-Why's that?

50
00:06:22.925 --> 00:06:24.675
Jules asked me for help.

51
00:06:24.676 --> 00:06:27.386
I blew her off first and then yelled at her.

52
00:06:27.387 --> 00:06:30.223
Don't beat yourself up. I straight up left her in the mine.

53
00:06:30.224 --> 00:06:32.517
What happened?
-She was trying to save people.

54
00:06:32.518 --> 00:06:35.604
Obviously.
-They won't let you in.

55
00:06:51.828 --> 00:06:53.621
Yo. Emerson.

56
00:06:53.622 --> 00:06:55.040
She's still breathing.

57
00:06:56.250 --> 00:06:57.650
Damn.

58
00:07:02.631 --> 00:07:06.760
Alright. Right here. Just breathe. You're good.

59
00:07:11.807 --> 00:07:13.207
We gotta roll.

60
00:07:19.898 --> 00:07:21.298
Sheriff.

61
00:07:34.329 --> 00:07:38.708
Sup. What do you need?
-Need you to confirm it was rat poison.

62
00:07:38.709 --> 00:07:41.252
Can't do that.
-Need more time?

63
00:07:41.253 --> 00:07:43.053
Nah. she wasn't poisoned.

64
00:07:43.964 --> 00:07:47.925
I got a dozen cases tonight where the cause of death was poison gas.

65
00:07:47.926 --> 00:07:51.762
Their lungs are completely wrecked. Hers are totally fine.

66
00:07:51.763 --> 00:07:55.763
What got her then?
-She took a massive hit to the head. Hard.

67
00:07:55.976 --> 00:07:58.728
Probably with a chunk of rebar.

68
00:07:58.729 --> 00:08:00.813
The wound's got a ribbed pattern.

69
00:08:00.814 --> 00:08:03.942
When?
-Looks like days ago.

70
00:08:07.863 --> 00:08:09.197
Where'd you find her?

71
00:08:09.198 --> 00:08:12.783
A crew was sweeping a sealed tunnel just to be safe.

72
00:08:12.784 --> 00:08:14.702
She was tucked way in the back.

73
00:08:14.703 --> 00:08:18.903
Was she down there for some reason and got caught in a cave-in?

74
00:08:19.499 --> 00:08:21.876
Rebar…
-Her lungs are untouched.

75
00:08:21.877 --> 00:08:24.010
She didn't kick it in the mine.

76
00:08:24.379 --> 00:08:27.381
I'm seeing plenty of people who died down there.

77
00:08:27.382 --> 00:08:29.782
They've always got dust in their lungs.

78
00:08:32.596 --> 00:08:34.597
She was hidden there.

79
00:08:39.770 --> 00:08:41.730
Let me see the wound.

80
00:08:42.940 --> 00:08:46.527
Billings to Deputy Murphy.
-Go ahead.

81
00:08:47.236 --> 00:08:51.948
If you spot Carla McLain. hit me up. I wanna talk about her student.

82
00:08:51.949 --> 00:08:53.349
Is she back yet?

83
00:09:02.209 --> 00:09:04.962
Okay. Not what I expected.

84
00:09:06.380 --> 00:09:08.173
You definitely don't live here.

85
00:09:09.842 --> 00:09:11.260
What makes you say that?

86
00:09:12.094 --> 00:09:16.932
You whip a 30-year-old Saab. And not ironically.

87
00:09:19.643 --> 00:09:21.854
This is different.

88
00:09:22.729 --> 00:09:26.817
I did help pick out the furniture. though.

89
00:09:31.655 --> 00:09:33.055
For who?

90
00:09:35.242 --> 00:09:38.036
Palmer. My ex.

91
00:09:39.288 --> 00:09:44.125
They're cool with you just walking right in?

92
00:09:44.126 --> 00:09:45.961
He's out in South Sudan.

93
00:09:52.843 --> 00:09:54.243
Shoes off.

94
00:10:09.443 --> 00:10:13.654
When a vibe dies with me. I wipe out every single trace of it.

95
00:10:13.655 --> 00:10:17.659
Yet he's got a massive pic of you hanging on his wall.

96
00:10:19.077 --> 00:10:21.329
Yeah. That's not Palmer.

97
00:10:21.330 --> 00:10:23.749
How so?
-He's not petty like that.

98
00:10:25.083 --> 00:10:26.417
So that's your type?

99
00:10:26.418 --> 00:10:30.685
Non-petty Pulitzer winners?
-Jesus. It wasn't a date.

100
00:10:34.218 --> 00:10:36.818
Any food?
-Make yourself at home.

101
00:10:37.429 --> 00:10:39.680
Where were you before you got here?

102
00:10:39.681 --> 00:10:42.058
Just wandering around. You?

103
00:10:42.059 --> 00:10:45.436
At the office.
-What office? You got canned.

104
00:10:45.437 --> 00:10:48.232
Still had my badge. Wanted a computer.

105
00:10:48.357 --> 00:10:52.527
Alright. I tracked down Steve's address.

106
00:10:52.528 --> 00:10:55.029
Turns out that was his real name. Steven Price.

107
00:10:55.030 --> 00:10:57.740
Found his digits. I think.

108
00:10:57.741 --> 00:11:01.410
That number was dead.
-Wrong number then?

109
00:11:01.411 --> 00:11:04.539
Then I called Charlotte's squad leader's dad.

110
00:11:04.540 --> 00:11:08.140
Mr Alameda.
-Yeah. That number was dead too.

111
00:11:09.336 --> 00:11:11.603
That number was working two days ago.

112
00:11:13.423 --> 00:11:15.342
What kind of people are we dealing with?

113
00:11:19.721 --> 00:11:21.321
We going to the cops?

114
00:11:22.349 --> 00:11:25.882
Pretty sure these folks make sure that does zero good.

115
00:11:27.396 --> 00:11:29.147
Two years past its prime.

116
00:11:32.025 --> 00:11:33.425
Nah. stop. Gross.

117
00:11:34.194 --> 00:11:35.594
Here.

118
00:11:37.155 --> 00:11:39.622
You just had that on you?
-What's our next move?

119
00:11:41.201 --> 00:11:42.601
Can we even do anything?

120
00:11:43.370 --> 00:11:45.903
Without that recording. our hands are tied.

121
00:11:46.248 --> 00:11:50.335
He mentioned some Moldovan guy recorded the radio comms.

122
00:11:52.421 --> 00:11:54.882
If we figure out who that was...

123
00:11:55.382 --> 00:11:58.760
maybe we can snag the recording and leak it.

124
00:12:00.721 --> 00:12:02.931
We don't know a thing about that person.

125
00:12:11.064 --> 00:12:13.983
Remember how Steve was playing chess?

126
00:12:13.984 --> 00:12:17.695
Yeah? His whole mood shifted when it was his turn.

127
00:12:17.696 --> 00:12:19.113
Something was up there.

128
00:12:19.114 --> 00:12:23.493
He had mate lined up and then just straight up exposed his king.

129
00:12:24.161 --> 00:12:28.094
Maybe he got distracted.
-What if he didn't want to win?

130
00:12:29.082 --> 00:12:32.215
What if that was how he communicated?
-What do you mean?

131
00:12:35.923 --> 00:12:39.056
When Snowden leaked those NSA docs back in '13...

132
00:12:39.551 --> 00:12:42.637
turns out agents were using World of Warcraft...

133
00:12:42.638 --> 00:12:44.805
to infiltrate terror cells.

134
00:12:44.806 --> 00:12:49.311
They thought terrorists were talking through online games.

135
00:12:50.312 --> 00:12:51.979
What would that even mean then?

136
00:12:52.606 --> 00:12:57.402
I dunno. 'The king'…
'The king has fallen'?

137
00:12:58.111 --> 00:12:59.695
Doesn't even matter.

138
00:12:59.696 --> 00:13:03.896
If we know who his opponent was. we got a lead.

139
00:13:04.159 --> 00:13:05.759
How do we figure that out?

140
00:13:06.828 --> 00:13:11.583
Alright. I caught the last bit of his username.

141
00:13:13.544 --> 00:13:18.006
It was something like...

142
00:13:20.843 --> 00:13:22.261
'Bigfoot lives'.

143
00:13:26.223 --> 00:13:27.623
Ridiculous.

144
00:13:29.059 --> 00:13:32.396
Well. cool.
-Whatever. That's what I saw.

145
00:13:35.023 --> 00:13:36.232
What?

146
00:13:36.233 --> 00:13:38.700
You're pretty good at this. Nancy Drew.

147
00:13:40.404 --> 00:13:42.405
Nah. don't call me that.

148
00:13:42.406 --> 00:13:45.199
Did they call you that in school? Is that a sore spot?

149
00:13:45.200 --> 00:13:46.952
Wanna say that again?

150
00:13:48.036 --> 00:13:50.455
I'll merk you. While you're sleeping.

151
00:14:20.068 --> 00:14:23.112
Lukas fucking Kyle.

152
00:14:23.113 --> 00:14:24.948
I heard you were looking for me.

153
00:14:26.200 --> 00:14:29.953
Alright. Hate to break it to you. but I got some bad news.

154
00:14:32.080 --> 00:14:33.480
What's that?

155
00:14:34.249 --> 00:14:37.582
You and your Outsiders keep shouting that outside is totally safe.

156
00:14:38.462 --> 00:14:41.423
It actually is.
-Nah. it seriously isn't.

157
00:14:42.508 --> 00:14:45.241
Whatever you're seeing on those cafeteria screens…

158
00:14:45.802 --> 00:14:47.554
That's what it actually looks like.

159
00:14:55.646 --> 00:14:58.357
Damn.

160
00:15:01.527 --> 00:15:06.405
You got bought out. So you've been living it up Upstairs in some luxury pad this whole time.

161
00:15:06.406 --> 00:15:10.993
I was down in the mine.
-I saw that cleaning video. you clown.

162
00:15:10.994 --> 00:15:12.746
I know they're lying.

163
00:15:13.330 --> 00:15:16.333
Outside is literally a paradise.

164
00:15:17.167 --> 00:15:23.215
They're projecting that video straight into the helmets to trick people into actually cleaning.

165
00:15:29.471 --> 00:15:30.871
A video inside the helmet?

166
00:15:43.360 --> 00:15:46.027
You buying this?
-Why would he lie?

167
00:15:46.238 --> 00:15:47.655
'Why would he lie?'

168
00:15:47.656 --> 00:15:49.056
Are you serious…
-Shit.

169
00:15:49.616 --> 00:15:51.016
What are you doing?

170
00:15:51.743 --> 00:15:54.143
Enforcers everywhere. They're hunting someone down.

171
00:15:55.080 --> 00:15:58.249
I don't give a damn if you believe me.

172
00:15:58.250 --> 00:16:02.753
They saved my life. and they just wanted me to talk to you. I'm done now.

173
00:16:02.754 --> 00:16:03.838
I'm out.
-Nah.

174
00:16:03.839 --> 00:16:05.590
Yeah. back to your palace.

175
00:16:05.591 --> 00:16:08.134
Yo. Juliette tracked me down in the mine.

176
00:16:08.135 --> 00:16:09.385
I'm gonna go find her.

177
00:16:09.386 --> 00:16:12.014
Back up.
-Nobody's going anywhere. Stay put.

178
00:16:12.973 --> 00:16:14.056
Shit.

179
00:16:14.057 --> 00:16:16.143
Security. Open up.

180
00:16:17.102 --> 00:16:18.687
Security. Open up.

181
00:16:19.897 --> 00:16:21.398
Security. Open up.

182
00:16:24.776 --> 00:16:26.576
Now you gotta stick with us.

183
00:16:30.532 --> 00:16:33.993
Stop.
-My girl is in there. I gotta get to her.

184
00:16:33.994 --> 00:16:36.537
It's locked down tight.
Nobody gets in or out.

185
00:16:36.538 --> 00:16:38.164
And now back up.

186
00:16:38.165 --> 00:16:40.125
Or what?
-Hey. Shirl.

187
00:16:44.087 --> 00:16:45.687
We tried.

188
00:16:47.466 --> 00:16:50.301
What if she kicks the bucket?
And we never see her again?

189
00:16:50.302 --> 00:16:53.597
You definitely won't see her if you get locked up.

190
00:16:55.224 --> 00:16:56.624
Let me talk to him.

191
00:17:03.232 --> 00:17:04.733
Just wanna introduce myself.

192
00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:06.800
Name's Knox.

193
00:17:07.069 --> 00:17:08.611
I'm Head of Mechanical.

194
00:17:08.612 --> 00:17:12.449
This friend of mine goes way back with the mayor since childhood.

195
00:17:12.574 --> 00:17:16.203
She just wants to drop a quick hello. and then she'll bounce.

196
00:17:17.454 --> 00:17:18.854
Head of Mechanical?

197
00:17:20.082 --> 00:17:21.615
Leader of the rebellion.

198
00:17:22.917 --> 00:17:26.296
I was down by the generator. With all that gunpowder.

199
00:17:26.839 --> 00:17:31.239
I said we should stash all of you right there next to the gunpowder.

200
00:17:32.177 --> 00:17:33.577
And then light it up.

201
00:17:34.680 --> 00:17:36.080
What do you think?

202
00:17:42.020 --> 00:17:43.420
I think...

203
00:17:44.481 --> 00:17:46.081
you're allowed to think whatever you want.

204
00:17:49.236 --> 00:17:50.779
Here's what I think.

205
00:17:57.536 --> 00:17:58.936
Shit.

206
00:18:23.061 --> 00:18:26.439
We got a problem.
Nichols is somewhere on this floor.

207
00:18:26.440 --> 00:18:31.173
Maybe with the nurse. Every camera down here is fried.

208
00:18:31.987 --> 00:18:35.156
You take that hallway. You take this one.

209
00:18:35.157 --> 00:18:37.618
Don't forget: keep it on the down low.

210
00:18:54.676 --> 00:18:56.594
How did this happen. Rob? How?

211
00:18:56.595 --> 00:18:59.555
We picked that nurse ourselves.
You called her loyal.

212
00:18:59.556 --> 00:19:02.642
She always followed her orders.
-Not anymore. she isn't.

213
00:19:02.643 --> 00:19:05.937
And now…
-She probably sensed what you came to do.

214
00:19:05.938 --> 00:19:07.438
If we blow this chance…

215
00:19:07.439 --> 00:19:09.191
We won't.
-How?

216
00:19:09.942 --> 00:19:12.318
I know that nurse pretty well.

217
00:19:12.319 --> 00:19:16.239
If they're running off. I know exactly where she's taking Nichols.

218
00:19:16.240 --> 00:19:18.908
Where?
-She's got fam downstairs.

219
00:19:18.909 --> 00:19:20.701
Send enforcers.

220
00:19:20.702 --> 00:19:23.747
Camille. we gotta handle this quietly.

221
00:19:26.333 --> 00:19:27.733
I'll lead the way.

222
00:19:28.585 --> 00:19:30.718
We gotta wrap this up tonight.

223
00:19:31.088 --> 00:19:33.882
I'll deal with her myself.

224
00:19:47.604 --> 00:19:51.357
Johnny. don't use the radio.
-Shoot me a text.

225
00:19:51.358 --> 00:19:54.735
Send people to the floors above and below us. too.

226
00:19:54.736 --> 00:19:57.989
When Emerson comes to. I wanna know what she remembers.

227
00:19:57.990 --> 00:20:00.700
She's still breathing and she pulled off a breakout.

228
00:20:00.701 --> 00:20:03.619
Oh. shit.
-Sims and his wife are trying to ice her.

229
00:20:03.620 --> 00:20:05.496
What? Why?

230
00:20:05.497 --> 00:20:06.897
No clue.

231
00:20:10.335 --> 00:20:11.735
I gotta trail him.

232
00:20:12.087 --> 00:20:16.591
Yo. Stop flapping your gums.
Step away from the prisoner. or you're coming with us.

233
00:20:16.592 --> 00:20:19.261
I was just saying this is what you get.

234
00:20:28.478 --> 00:20:30.313
You got the key?

235
00:20:30.314 --> 00:20:32.523
They're gonna spot us the second we walk out.

236
00:20:32.524 --> 00:20:34.525
We're not taking the door.

237
00:20:34.526 --> 00:20:37.737
I grew up here and found out back in the day...

238
00:20:37.738 --> 00:20:41.738
somebody got sick of having to walk all the way to the stairs.

239
00:20:45.245 --> 00:20:46.871
Alright. let's move. We're out.

240
00:20:46.872 --> 00:20:48.497
Hey. No.

241
00:20:48.498 --> 00:20:50.791
My bad. I'm the reason your memory is coming back.

242
00:20:50.792 --> 00:20:53.920
I took away your pills.
-Nah. I spit 'em out.

243
00:20:53.921 --> 00:20:56.380
I had to swap 'em out way before that.

244
00:20:56.381 --> 00:20:58.257
By whose orders?
-We don't got time.

245
00:20:58.258 --> 00:21:01.058
Your choice: roll with me. or take your chances with the enforcers.

246
00:21:20.072 --> 00:21:21.472
Hello?

247
00:21:30.374 --> 00:21:34.293
Oh. my bad. Thought I was solo.
She's totally harmless. don't sweat it.

248
00:21:34.294 --> 00:21:35.694
Sheriff Billings.

249
00:21:36.880 --> 00:21:41.259
You're the first face I've seen. Sheriffs don't really swing by much.

250
00:21:41.260 --> 00:21:42.761
Especially at night.

251
00:21:44.096 --> 00:21:46.098
I'm looking for Carla McLain.

252
00:21:46.890 --> 00:21:50.101
McLain? She hasn't been around here in months.

253
00:21:50.102 --> 00:21:52.311
I was expecting her.
-Gotcha.

254
00:21:52.312 --> 00:21:53.897
Later. sheriff.

255
00:21:56.316 --> 00:21:57.860
What's your name?
-Mike.

256
00:21:58.485 --> 00:22:00.237
Mike what?
-Davidson.

257
00:22:01.321 --> 00:22:04.490
Orla Kent's man. Her sister dropped your name.

258
00:22:04.491 --> 00:22:06.243
Oh. Yeah. right.

259
00:22:07.244 --> 00:22:08.829
Sheila. Yeah.

260
00:22:10.122 --> 00:22:12.164
Orla turn up yet?

261
00:22:12.165 --> 00:22:13.565
Hopefully soon.

262
00:22:15.002 --> 00:22:18.087
When was the last time you saw her?
-Right here. at work.

263
00:22:18.088 --> 00:22:20.924
At Essential Supplies.
-How was her vibe?

264
00:22:21.049 --> 00:22:22.675
What?
-Her mood.

265
00:22:22.676 --> 00:22:26.554
What she said.
-Oh. yeah. She seemed super upbeat.

266
00:22:26.555 --> 00:22:31.142
She'd just gotten back from that council meeting. Heading home.

267
00:22:31.143 --> 00:22:35.354
Did you tag along?
-Nah. I was tossing a ball with Dandy.

268
00:22:35.355 --> 00:22:39.555
It's a huge open room. Great for throwing a ball way out.

269
00:22:40.319 --> 00:22:43.487
I said bye. Haven't seen her since.

270
00:22:43.488 --> 00:22:45.221
You don't seem super stressed about it.

271
00:22:48.243 --> 00:22:51.663
Orla always gets slept on. Even by her own family.

272
00:22:52.497 --> 00:22:57.419
She's probably. like. caught up in all sorts of stuff even I don't know about.

273
00:23:02.090 --> 00:23:04.510
Thanks for your time.
-See ya.

274
00:23:14.853 --> 00:23:16.920
They're straight out of medical.

275
00:23:20.067 --> 00:23:21.944
Here. Take it. Grab this.

276
00:23:25.447 --> 00:23:28.408
By order of Judicial. open up.

277
00:23:33.872 --> 00:23:35.272
Open up.

278
00:23:37.084 --> 00:23:39.419
Alright. Deep breaths. Okay?

279
00:23:40.087 --> 00:23:42.840
Listen. I'll draw them away from you.

280
00:23:43.715 --> 00:23:48.010
Once it's safe. head over to the pump room on 75.

281
00:23:48.011 --> 00:23:50.555
What? Okay.
-Alright? Level 75. Bet.

282
00:23:50.556 --> 00:23:52.391
Wait. Yo.

283
00:23:57.145 --> 00:23:59.022
The nurse. Grab her.

284
00:24:00.190 --> 00:24:03.901
No. Get your hands off me.
-Where's the mayor?

285
00:24:03.902 --> 00:24:06.405
In medical.
-Show me.

286
00:24:37.644 --> 00:24:39.044
Daniel?

287
00:24:47.154 --> 00:24:48.554
He dipped.

288
00:24:49.615 --> 00:24:51.015
Straight up bounced.

289
00:24:57.331 --> 00:24:58.731
Hey.

290
00:24:58.916 --> 00:25:00.709
Hey.
-What?

291
00:25:01.919 --> 00:25:05.255
Thought you chickened out.
-Miss me?

292
00:25:07.674 --> 00:25:09.074
Where'd you even run off to?

293
00:25:09.885 --> 00:25:10.968
No way.

294
00:25:10.969 --> 00:25:14.180
We got fed agents on our tail...

295
00:25:14.181 --> 00:25:15.973
and you're out here getting donuts?

296
00:25:15.974 --> 00:25:17.726
And pastries.

297
00:25:19.102 --> 00:25:20.502
Absolute goofball.

298
00:25:20.938 --> 00:25:22.563
There's a shop right around the corner.

299
00:25:22.564 --> 00:25:26.108
They said I couldn't use the phone unless I bought something. So there's that.

300
00:25:26.109 --> 00:25:29.195
You can't call Charlotte.
-Not Charlotte.

301
00:25:29.196 --> 00:25:31.948
Go change your fit. we got somewhere to be.

302
00:25:31.949 --> 00:25:33.349
What? Where?

303
00:25:35.410 --> 00:25:36.810
The Pentagon.

304
00:26:12.990 --> 00:26:14.950
Listen.

305
00:26:18.245 --> 00:26:19.645
Go.

306
00:26:20.163 --> 00:26:21.563
Move.

307
00:26:23.667 --> 00:26:25.067
Run.

308
00:26:28.589 --> 00:26:32.092
They're gonna clip you.

309
00:26:33.218 --> 00:26:35.428
How'd he even know where I was headed?

310
00:26:35.429 --> 00:26:37.763
We can stash you down in Mechanical.

311
00:26:37.764 --> 00:26:39.932
I gotta find Lukas.

312
00:26:39.933 --> 00:26:41.393
Lukas is dead.

313
00:26:41.894 --> 00:26:43.294
Nah. I…

314
00:26:44.188 --> 00:26:47.399
Nah. I talked to him. I saw him down in the mine.

315
00:26:49.610 --> 00:26:51.903
Take me wherever you dropped him off.

316
00:26:51.904 --> 00:26:53.771
The dig site is locked down.

317
00:26:54.907 --> 00:26:57.174
Fine. get me as close as you can.

318
00:26:59.620 --> 00:27:01.020
Whatever.

319
00:27:08.629 --> 00:27:10.963
Kenny G in the flesh.

320
00:27:10.964 --> 00:27:13.634
Look at that. Sam the Ram.

321
00:27:15.344 --> 00:27:17.762
Looking good.
-My assistant. Helen.

322
00:27:17.763 --> 00:27:19.263
Nice to meet you.
-Sam Ramsey.

323
00:27:19.264 --> 00:27:21.349
Wanna take a walk?
-Yep.

324
00:27:21.350 --> 00:27:22.517
How do you guys know each other?

325
00:27:22.518 --> 00:27:24.769
Army days.
-That too.

326
00:27:24.770 --> 00:27:27.063
We used to jam in a band together. too.

327
00:27:27.064 --> 00:27:29.316
A band?
-The Lost Boys.

328
00:27:31.735 --> 00:27:33.611
We played '80s tunes.

329
00:27:33.612 --> 00:27:36.239
Your boy here used to rip the sax...

330
00:27:36.240 --> 00:27:39.951
before we turned into boring desk jockeys.
-You work at the Pentagon.

331
00:27:39.952 --> 00:27:43.579
I beg for votes.
-So that's what you're here for.

332
00:27:43.580 --> 00:27:46.207
He wants me to hack the voting machines for him.

333
00:27:46.208 --> 00:27:48.293
Nice try. K.G.

334
00:27:50.879 --> 00:27:52.129
I need some backup.

335
00:27:52.130 --> 00:27:55.008
You wanted to talk cybersecurity.

336
00:27:55.592 --> 00:27:57.059
You gotta track someone down.

337
00:28:01.181 --> 00:28:02.581
Who kind of person?

338
00:28:03.475 --> 00:28:05.309
Some online chess player.

339
00:28:05.310 --> 00:28:09.522
All we got is his opponent's username.

340
00:28:09.523 --> 00:28:12.066
Doesn't sound like government business.

341
00:28:12.067 --> 00:28:16.112
My sister Charlotte was on that mission in Iran. It went totally sideways.

342
00:28:16.113 --> 00:28:18.698
She's the sole survivor.

343
00:28:18.699 --> 00:28:20.099
Shit.

344
00:28:20.659 --> 00:28:23.536
Is she okay?
-She's got amnesia.

345
00:28:23.537 --> 00:28:26.039
She had bad vibes about the mission.

346
00:28:26.915 --> 00:28:29.458
There was a recording of their comms.

347
00:28:29.459 --> 00:28:31.879
That's encrypted.
-This isn't.

348
00:28:32.796 --> 00:28:34.505
We heard it. 20 seconds.

349
00:28:34.506 --> 00:28:36.906
That was her main concern.
-Wait.

350
00:28:38.635 --> 00:28:41.555
What'd you actually hear. Dan?

351
00:28:46.435 --> 00:28:47.935
Well?
-Planes...

352
00:28:47.936 --> 00:28:52.024
that weren't being flown by pilots anymore.

353
00:28:52.983 --> 00:28:56.486
Our contact is ghosted and so is the recording.

354
00:28:58.197 --> 00:28:59.989
You're not an assistant. are you?

355
00:28:59.990 --> 00:29:02.785
Something super messed up went down on that mission.

356
00:29:02.910 --> 00:29:05.536
We need that recording.
-And you think...

357
00:29:05.537 --> 00:29:08.498
I'm gonna help you leak state secrets?

358
00:29:10.626 --> 00:29:12.026
I got a sister too.

359
00:29:12.836 --> 00:29:15.172
And a wife and kids.

360
00:29:16.798 --> 00:29:20.885
And I took an oath. Plus I signed like a million NDAs.

361
00:29:20.886 --> 00:29:24.013
But you know that. You did too.

362
00:29:24.014 --> 00:29:26.641
I gotta take polygraph tests.

363
00:29:26.642 --> 00:29:28.017
Every six months.
-Sam.

364
00:29:28.018 --> 00:29:29.418
I get it.
-For real?

365
00:29:40.531 --> 00:29:44.264
Listen. If it was my sister. I'd want to know too.

366
00:29:45.327 --> 00:29:48.872
But she's an insurance agent. so that ain't happening.

367
00:29:53.293 --> 00:29:56.693
If you ever wanna jam again. like old times...

368
00:29:57.881 --> 00:29:59.281
give me a ring.

369
00:29:59.633 --> 00:30:01.927
Alright. I gotta bounce.

370
00:30:10.394 --> 00:30:12.396
Okay. Now what?

371
00:30:18.986 --> 00:30:20.386
What?

372
00:30:21.071 --> 00:30:23.538
I spotted that dude at Alameda's funeral.

373
00:30:26.034 --> 00:30:28.234
I saw him when I got canned.

374
00:30:29.121 --> 00:30:30.521
For real?

375
00:30:34.376 --> 00:30:36.253
Hey. Daniel. Helen.

376
00:30:36.962 --> 00:30:38.562
Wanna grab some coffee?

377
00:30:39.715 --> 00:30:41.115
My treat.

378
00:30:45.345 --> 00:30:47.556
Y'all seriously want nothing?

379
00:30:48.682 --> 00:30:50.057
Helen. you want anything?

380
00:30:50.058 --> 00:30:51.350
Nah. I'm good.

381
00:30:51.351 --> 00:30:54.146
No need. Appreciate the offer though.

382
00:30:56.106 --> 00:31:00.276
Let's cut to the chase.
-Where's our Baltimore contact?

383
00:31:00.277 --> 00:31:03.155
Is he dead. or getting tortured somewhere?

384
00:31:05.574 --> 00:31:08.910
Steven Price currently holds a very coveted gig...

385
00:31:08.911 --> 00:31:12.311
at Radford Group. a cybersecurity think tank.

386
00:31:14.166 --> 00:31:18.419
You're probably thinking of Mr. Alameda's dad.

387
00:31:18.420 --> 00:31:19.820
After the funeral...

388
00:31:20.297 --> 00:31:23.966
he got a sweet loan for his brother's shop...

389
00:31:23.967 --> 00:31:26.177
out in Cali.
-In exchange for what?

390
00:31:26.178 --> 00:31:27.578
Hear me out.

391
00:31:28.096 --> 00:31:32.643
Y'all are a threat to something super important.

392
00:31:34.853 --> 00:31:36.313
What's your name?

393
00:31:37.648 --> 00:31:41.484
I like knowing who's screwing me over. even if…
-I represent...

394
00:31:41.485 --> 00:31:45.489
people who can hook you up with a second chance.

395
00:31:47.074 --> 00:31:51.578
The Times must've been your dream job back in the day. right?

396
00:31:56.416 --> 00:31:59.001
I talked to the editor-in-chief.

397
00:31:59.002 --> 00:32:00.920
He's down to meet with you...

398
00:32:00.921 --> 00:32:04.121
despite your rep for journalistic fraud.

399
00:32:04.675 --> 00:32:10.222
It'd be a waste for your talent to go down the drain over one little mistake.

400
00:32:17.062 --> 00:32:19.605
Screw you. You're the reason I got fired.

401
00:32:19.606 --> 00:32:22.149
I'm just one phone call away.

402
00:32:22.150 --> 00:32:23.550
Think about it.

403
00:32:25.070 --> 00:32:29.575
Alright. So how much cash and perks are you gonna throw my way?

404
00:32:30.993 --> 00:32:33.326
In your case. this isn't about you.

405
00:32:35.497 --> 00:32:39.297
What a sick threat. Cutting off Charlotte's treatment.

406
00:32:40.878 --> 00:32:42.278
Yeah. Pretty messed up.

407
00:32:43.046 --> 00:32:44.756
What?
-Pardon?

408
00:32:45.465 --> 00:32:48.302
That sounded like a 'but' was coming.

409
00:32:49.636 --> 00:32:52.430
Well. I mean. it wasn't really a threat.

410
00:32:52.431 --> 00:32:54.140
He. like…

411
00:32:54.141 --> 00:32:58.060
he mentioned her trauma therapy is pricey...

412
00:32:58.061 --> 00:33:00.479
and isn't covered…
-My bad.

413
00:33:00.480 --> 00:33:02.774
I don't really see the difference.

414
00:33:07.404 --> 00:33:10.364
I can… I'm a congressman.

415
00:33:10.365 --> 00:33:13.898
I can spill what we know to the media.
-And that is?

416
00:33:14.828 --> 00:33:17.205
We know about the mission.
-Got any proof?

417
00:33:17.206 --> 00:33:19.957
I can subpoena the records. And the tape.

418
00:33:19.958 --> 00:33:21.835
Daniel. they won't find a damn thing.

419
00:33:36.600 --> 00:33:38.018
You want that job.

420
00:33:38.852 --> 00:33:40.252
Pardon?

421
00:33:40.521 --> 00:33:45.108
Maybe you should tell 'em about that journalistic fraud.

422
00:33:47.361 --> 00:33:51.573
If you'd scrolled past my LinkedIn. you'd already know.

423
00:33:51.698 --> 00:33:54.868
And obviously I want the job. you goody-two-shoes.

424
00:33:55.619 --> 00:34:00.752
But I also want solid care for Charlotte. She's your sister. but she's my source.

425
00:34:01.416 --> 00:34:03.960
What am I supposed to do now? Go back to my cubicle?

426
00:34:03.961 --> 00:34:06.094
How should I know?
-Like a lapdog?

427
00:34:14.221 --> 00:34:18.724
Whatever you do. please keep a low profile.

428
00:34:18.725 --> 00:34:22.271
They're definitely watching us.
-Jesus.

429
00:34:28.819 --> 00:34:30.219
What are you gonna do?

430
00:34:33.447 --> 00:34:36.514
My ex is out of town for a week. I'll crash there.

431
00:34:39.288 --> 00:34:40.688
I need to think.

432
00:34:41.581 --> 00:34:42.981
And you?

433
00:34:45.585 --> 00:34:47.503
I've missed a ton of work.

434
00:34:47.504 --> 00:34:50.424
Guess I'll go take care of that.

435
00:35:00.934 --> 00:35:02.334
Congressman.

436
00:35:36.011 --> 00:35:37.411
You know...

437
00:35:39.848 --> 00:35:44.352
they gave me those pills. The meds.

438
00:35:44.353 --> 00:35:46.604
They messed with my head.

439
00:35:46.605 --> 00:35:50.609
But I'm starting to actually care about people. Like Knox.

440
00:35:51.610 --> 00:35:55.277
I don't know why. but every time I see him. I just…

441
00:35:56.448 --> 00:36:01.327
Y'all weren't always homies.
-I'm just saying: with you. I feel like...

442
00:36:01.328 --> 00:36:04.128
if someone tried to hurt you. I'd…

443
00:36:06.375 --> 00:36:11.108
I don't know. I'd probably ice that person or something. That's what I meant.

444
00:36:14.341 --> 00:36:15.741
Whatever.

445
00:36:38.866 --> 00:36:41.034
Ossie.

446
00:36:43.829 --> 00:36:45.289
Hey. Shirley.

447
00:36:45.789 --> 00:36:48.124
What are you doing?
-We gotta head down.

448
00:36:48.125 --> 00:36:50.961
The crew's gonna be here.
-No. We gotta go right now.

449
00:36:51.461 --> 00:36:53.922
We're not heavy. I trust you.

450
00:36:58.927 --> 00:37:00.327
Mayor.

451
00:37:07.519 --> 00:37:12.982
Here's the deal: if anyone wants to head down in the next half hour. even enforcers...

452
00:37:12.983 --> 00:37:15.986
can you just say the equipment's busted?

453
00:37:16.570 --> 00:37:18.037
Like. telling them to wait?

454
00:37:21.575 --> 00:37:24.911
Yeah. Saying we got pulley issues.

455
00:37:24.912 --> 00:37:26.913
Might take a minute.
-Alright. Let's roll.

456
00:37:26.914 --> 00:37:28.314
Sick.

457
00:37:40.886 --> 00:37:43.055
Where were you all night?

458
00:37:43.722 --> 00:37:45.264
I was tailing Nichols.

459
00:37:45.265 --> 00:37:47.975
She went down with someone.

460
00:37:47.976 --> 00:37:50.811
Who?
-Her friend. I think. Shirley?

461
00:37:50.812 --> 00:37:52.648
Oh. shit.
-What?

462
00:37:53.649 --> 00:37:55.942
What?
-Why are you looking like that?

463
00:37:55.943 --> 00:37:58.402
Nothing. I know where Juliette's headed.

464
00:37:58.403 --> 00:38:00.071
Mechanical?
-Nah. deeper.

465
00:38:00.072 --> 00:38:01.822
That doesn't matter to us.

466
00:38:01.823 --> 00:38:05.118
Yes it does. it matters to everyone.

467
00:38:05.786 --> 00:38:07.745
I gotta stop her.
-No.

468
00:38:07.746 --> 00:38:09.205
Here we go again?

469
00:38:09.206 --> 00:38:12.334
Okay.
Y'all actually wanna know the truth?

470
00:38:12.835 --> 00:38:15.378
Ask Juliette.
-She don't know jack.

471
00:38:15.379 --> 00:38:18.312
She's popping amnesia pills. She didn't even recognize us.

472
00:38:18.465 --> 00:38:22.052
Might remember now. She spotted me in the mine.

473
00:38:30.936 --> 00:38:32.336
How do we get down there?

474
00:38:33.021 --> 00:38:35.983
There's a way. You ain't gonna like it.

475
00:38:36.692 --> 00:38:38.559
Ignore him. You love this stuff.

476
00:38:44.199 --> 00:38:46.034
Hey. Get this trash out of here.

477
00:38:51.206 --> 00:38:53.333
What are you doing in my office?

478
00:38:55.210 --> 00:38:56.711
SUPPLY APPRENTICE

479
00:38:56.712 --> 00:38:58.838
My bad. didn't see your badge.

480
00:38:58.839 --> 00:39:00.239
Your office?

481
00:39:00.674 --> 00:39:04.074
Since when?
-Since the current apprentice took off.

482
00:39:04.511 --> 00:39:08.557
And McLain's totally MIA. Somebody's gotta run the show.

483
00:39:09.474 --> 00:39:11.074
And that 'somebody' is you?

484
00:39:12.811 --> 00:39:14.645
I am the former apprentice.

485
00:39:14.646 --> 00:39:17.482
So I'm way more qualified.

486
00:39:18.066 --> 00:39:22.466
And unlike the new girl. I never just ghost.

487
00:39:22.863 --> 00:39:24.656
You got beef with Orla Kent?

488
00:39:25.157 --> 00:39:28.159
She stole my gig.
-You Glenda?

489
00:39:28.160 --> 00:39:30.827
Spot on.
-Did she steal your man too?

490
00:39:34.833 --> 00:39:39.545
Mike Davidson is about as much Orla's man as you are mine. Sheriff.

491
00:39:39.546 --> 00:39:41.756
He thinks everybody's obsessed with him.

492
00:39:41.757 --> 00:39:46.011
And he's a total tool. so sometimes he just has to flex to prove it.

493
00:39:47.596 --> 00:39:51.141
So she didn't steal Mike. just your job?

494
00:39:53.143 --> 00:39:57.876
I shouldn't be petty. When I lost my apprentice gig…

495
00:39:59.608 --> 00:40:01.008
It was a relief.

496
00:40:04.696 --> 00:40:06.096
Why?

497
00:40:06.323 --> 00:40:07.723
Because...

498
00:40:08.659 --> 00:40:11.036
it meant I could actually hang out at home.

499
00:40:12.663 --> 00:40:15.165
On the 69th floor. In the mine.

500
00:40:15.958 --> 00:40:18.418
Ed Harwood is your…
-Dad.

501
00:40:19.795 --> 00:40:21.630
The absolute legend.

502
00:40:24.883 --> 00:40:26.683
Somebody in trouble?

503
00:40:30.055 --> 00:40:32.522
When was the last time you saw Orla Kent?

504
00:40:39.022 --> 00:40:40.422
Wait.

505
00:40:42.192 --> 00:40:45.259
I know this place.
-You used to hang here all the time.

506
00:40:45.612 --> 00:40:47.012
You had a boyfriend.

507
00:40:55.163 --> 00:40:56.563
George.

508
00:40:58.208 --> 00:40:59.793
Right?

509
00:41:01.670 --> 00:41:06.670
Y'all used to sneak to the hollow. You never talked about him. but I knew.

510
00:41:11.096 --> 00:41:13.765
Told you so. My bad.

511
00:41:15.350 --> 00:41:16.601
What are you doing?

512
00:41:16.602 --> 00:41:18.394
LOCKED

513
00:41:18.395 --> 00:41:20.022
What?
-Hold up.

514
00:41:26.862 --> 00:41:28.780
Hey. Can you turn off the light?

515
00:41:33.702 --> 00:41:35.102
Come check this out.

516
00:41:36.371 --> 00:41:38.332
Here.
-What?

517
00:41:39.166 --> 00:41:40.566
Right here.

518
00:41:45.756 --> 00:41:48.717
There's gotta be a latch somewhere. or…

519
00:41:50.135 --> 00:41:53.002
It's gotta open.
-What is this? Hang on.

520
00:41:59.561 --> 00:42:00.961
Wait.

521
00:42:09.238 --> 00:42:12.505
Walker said she locked it down.
-Guess not.

522
00:42:13.367 --> 00:42:14.825
Let me see.

523
00:42:14.826 --> 00:42:17.454
Take that. And close the door.

524
00:43:31.653 --> 00:43:35.653
WASHINGTON POST REPORTER FIRED FOR FAKE SOURCE

525
00:43:52.841 --> 00:43:54.241
Hello?

526
00:43:55.010 --> 00:43:56.410
Who's this?

527
00:43:56.887 --> 00:44:00.264
Hey. it's Congressman Daniel Keene.

528
00:44:00.265 --> 00:44:03.769
Who am I speaking with?
-K.G.. it's me.

529
00:44:09.399 --> 00:44:10.799
Sam?

530
00:44:11.985 --> 00:44:14.028
How…
-I'm on a burner.

531
00:44:14.029 --> 00:44:17.907
Nobody can trace it. But I gotta make it quick. so listen up.

532
00:44:17.908 --> 00:44:21.575
What you told me about your sister's mission was bugging me.

533
00:44:21.912 --> 00:44:25.749
Been stressing about it all week. Wanted to look into it.

534
00:44:26.834 --> 00:44:28.967
And it's straight-up wild.

535
00:44:29.461 --> 00:44:31.794
I found something insane.

536
00:44:52.943 --> 00:44:54.343
Helen. you in there?

537
00:44:58.699 --> 00:45:00.241
What are you doing here?

538
00:45:00.242 --> 00:45:02.618
Sam called. He did some digging.

539
00:45:02.619 --> 00:45:05.486
I thought he wouldn't help?
-He found something.

540
00:45:08.000 --> 00:45:10.752
I know you wanted to quit. but…

541
00:45:13.422 --> 00:45:18.427
I don't know how to pull this off by myself.

542
00:45:22.806 --> 00:45:24.932
This is it.
-You drive a minivan?

543
00:45:24.933 --> 00:45:27.666
Rented. From some guy who hangs up posters.

544
00:45:28.228 --> 00:45:30.396
Seemed like the lowest profile ride.

545
00:45:30.397 --> 00:45:32.106
Paid cash.
-Thanks.

546
00:45:32.107 --> 00:45:33.640
Might even be stolen.

547
00:46:26.578 --> 00:46:27.978
Hello?

548
00:46:39.216 --> 00:46:41.009
Hello. Juliette.
